#Approach:

**Sort List – Hinglish Approach (Merge Sort on Linked List)**

Is question me hume linked list ko **ascending order** me sort karna hai.
Array ki tarah direct indexing possible nahi hoti, isliye linked list ke liye **Merge Sort** best approach hota hai.

### Approach:

**1. Base case**
Agar list empty hai ya sirf 1 node hai, to vo already sorted hai.

**2. Middle find karo**
`slow` aur `fast` pointer use karke middle nikaalte hain.
Yaha `fast = head.next` se start kiya gaya hai taaki hume **left half ka last node** mile aur list properly 2 parts me split ho sake.

**3. List ko 2 halves me tod do**

* `leftHead = head`
* `rightHead = middle.next`
* `middle.next = null`

Ab original list do alag linked lists me split ho gayi.

**4. Recursively dono halves sort karo**

* left part ko sort karo
* right part ko sort karo

**5. Dono sorted halves merge karo**
`merge2()` function exactly merge two sorted lists ki tarah kaam karta hai:

* `t1` aur `t2` compare hote hain
* jo smaller node hota hai, usko result me attach kar dete hain
* end me bachi hui list directly attach kar dete hain

### Why Merge Sort?

Linked list me merge operation bahut efficiently ho jata hai using pointers, isliye merge sort most suitable hota hai.

### Complexity:

* **Time Complexity:** `O(n log n)`
* **Space Complexity:** `O(log n)` recursion stack

### One-line yaad rakhne wali logic:

> Middle find karo → list split karo → dono parts sort karo → merge karke final sorted list banao.


#Code:

/**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * public class ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode next;
 *     ListNode() {}
 *     ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }
 * }
 */
class Solution {

    private ListNode merge2(ListNode lHead, ListNode rHead){

        ListNode t1 = lHead;
        ListNode t2 = rHead;
        ListNode dummyNode = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode temp = dummyNode;

        while(t1 != null && t2 != null){
            if(t1.val < t2.val){
                temp.next = t1;
                temp = temp.next;
                t1 = t1.next;
            }
            else if(t1.val > t2.val){
                temp.next = t2;
                temp = temp.next;
                t2 = t2.next;
            }
            else{
                //if both are equal
                temp.next = t1;
                temp = temp.next;
                t1 = t1.next;
            }
        }

        //if t2 is exhausted
        while(t1 != null){
            temp.next = t1;
            temp = temp.next;
            t1 = t1.next;
        }
        //if t1 is exhausted
        while(t2 != null){
            temp.next = t2;
            temp = temp.next;
            t2 = t2.next;
        }
        return dummyNode.next;
    }

    private ListNode findMiddle(ListNode head){
        ListNode slow = head;
        ListNode fast = head.next;

        while(fast != null && fast.next != null){
            slow = slow.next;
            fast = fast.next.next;
        }
        return slow;
    }

    private ListNode mergeSort(ListNode head){
        if(head == null || head.next == null){
            return head;
        }

        ListNode middle = findMiddle(head);
        ListNode leftHead = head;
        ListNode rightHead = middle.next;
        middle.next = null;
        leftHead = mergeSort(leftHead);
        rightHead = mergeSort(rightHead);

        return merge2(leftHead, rightHead);
    }

    public ListNode sortList(ListNode head) {
        
        if(head == null || head.next == null){
            return head;
        }

        head = mergeSort(head);
        return head;
    }
}
